Albizia odoratissima

   Authority (L. f.) Benth.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
   Synonyms Acacia odoratissima (L. f.) Willd., Albizia odoratissima var.
   mollis Benth. ex Bak., Mimosa odoratissima L. f.
   Common names fragrant albizia, Ceylon rosewood, favas de Lazaro
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 2966

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Troup R 1921 pp 479-480 [USE, DRA, TEMP, RAIN, LIG]
   Voortman R 1994 (pers. comm.)
   KILLING T
   Seedlings are killed by frost, mature trees survive -1Â°C.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial deciduous tree. In northern India the leaves commence falling
   about December, and the new leaves appear in March-April.
   COMMON NAMES
   Black siris, Karmaru, Kali siris, Bansa, Bilkumbi, Bilwara, Karu vagai,
   Thitmagyi.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: Mimosa odoratissima. In the Himalayan mountains it
   can be found at elevations up to 1700 m. (pH estimated by the
   compiler).

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
